reasoning='To meet the specification of a folded-cascode OTA with a single external bias port (ibn10u) carrying a 10 µA DC current source, I designed an input NMOS differential pair (M1/M2) whose sources tie to the bias port. An internal NMOS tail transistor (Mtail) replicates that bias current and generates an internal gate bias node (netb) which is used to bias the PMOS cascode devices (P1/P2). The drains of the cascodes form two nodes (node1 and vout). A simple NMOS current mirror (M3/M4) between node1 and the single-ended output vout converts the differential currents to a single-ended output. All devices use the foundry models (tsmc18dN and tsmc18dP) and explicitly reference the ports VDD, VSS, ibn10u, vin, vip, and vout as required. The top-level instantiation follows the exact ordering from the template.' config=ConfigFile(netlist='// Library name: MP4
// Cell name: fc_ota
// View name: schematic
subckt fc_ota VDD VSS ibn10u vin vip vout
Mtail (ibn10u VSS netb netb) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
M1 (node1 vin ibn10u VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
M2 (vout vip ibn10u VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u
P1 (node1 netb VDD VDD) tsmc18dP w=40u l=0.18u
P2 (vout netb VDD VDD) tsmc18dP w=40u l=0.18u
M3 (node1 node1 VSS VSS) tsmc18dN w=20u l=0.18u
M4 (vout node1 VSS VSS) tsmc18dN w=20u l=0.18u
ends fc_ota
// Top-level instantiation
// Library name: MP4
// Cell name: dut
// View name: schematic
I1 (net1 net2 net5 net3 net4 net6) fc_ota')
